Cross References

  Hawaii health authority, see chapter 322H.

Attorney General Opinions

  The office of the governor is a constitutional office
established by §1 of article V of the state constitution and is not a principal
department of the state executive branch listed in this section; thus, any
agency that is not temporary and for special purposes cannot be validly placed
within the office of the governor.  Att. Gen Op. 96-1.

Case Notes

  Administrative agency is not a "person" under Civil
Rights Act, 42 USCA §1983.  396 F. Supp. 375.

  Presumption of constitutionality applies to policies set by
state agencies.  56 H. 601, 546 P.2d 1005.

